survey_response.review_text:
Dr. Kim is very experienced, ********* ******* *** extremely supportive. I visited her at Kosmodent for two of my major molar tooth fillings which were effortlessly and painlessly treated by her in a jiffy. For the same I was firstly suggested Temporary fillings and then Root Canals, X-Rays, Caps etc. complicated procedures by other reputed dentists in the city but Dr. Kim simply and artistically filled my two molars avoiding all unwanted complicated procedures. Kosmodent as a clinic is well equipped, very hygienic and offers state of the art services at affordable prices. Dr. Kim is very flexible in providing appointments and understands and adjusts her availability according to the busy corporate life of Bangalore.

Overall a very satisfying and amazing experience. Trusted and highly recommended.

review.practice_name: Kosmodent Dental Studio and Implant Centre

survey_response.review_text: I was suffering from this weird kind of pain in my jaws  neck and head for 2 years now ...it made my life miserable..I visited a lot of dentists but no one was able to diagnose my problem..I even checked with ENT , got an MRI for my brain done... nothing seemed to be helping me....on a friend's suggestion I visited Dr Kim ....she spoke to me about my eating , sleeping habits and posture...after a few examinations of my face,  my cause of my problem was diagnosed... treatment began and in a week's time it was also solved . I had been unnecessarily suffering for so long...The assurance that Dr.Kim gave and the depth of knowledge she has really helped me. Highly recommend.

review.practice_name: Kosmodent Dental Studio and Implant Centre

survey_response.review_text: I highly recommend Kosmodent Dental Studio. I had a problem of severe tooth erosion because of teeth grinding and had lost almost 50% of enamel volume across all teeth, and I also had multiple cavities, one which was so deep that one other dentist told me there was no way to save it. I was treated by Dr Kim, and had a full mouth rehabilitation using Zirconium implants. I started with just a root canal, but took Dr Kim's advise to go for a full reconstruction which I realised is a good investment for the rest of my life. She didn't put any pressure on me and gave me all options. Now I have my smile from college days (I am 41 now) and a much better bite. A few years later, I might have had to go for expensive implants. Thank you Dr Kim.

survey_response.review_text:
Have gone for a tooth extraction. Was quoted for Rs 800 for the same after seeing the tooth condition. Once the extraction was over, without any surgical removal. I was told that it was complex and hence will be Rs 2000. What can one do after the treatment has been done. An increase of 2.5 times without even informing the patient.

It is a day light loot. No bill given. I would like to be beware before going there and confirm the price.

P.S: The service isn't bad. But as a patient i deserve to know the price which you have taken almost 2.5 times without even informing once. And i still don't understand about complexity as it was non surgical extraction and everywhere else even the big chains are not charging Rs. 2000 for it.

survey_response.review_text: So basically my mother had to undergo a complete oral reconstruction as her tooth conditions were too bad. So we had consulted couple of doctors but were not satisfied until we met Dr. Kim. She suggested the best, economical, easy, painless, effective and quickest solution. The whole treatment just took us 2weeks while the other doctors quoted us atleast two months for the same treatment with 2x amount of the cost. My mom is very happy with the treatment.

review.practice_name: Kosmodent Multispeciality Dental Clinic and Implant Centre

survey_response.review_text:
I took my two sons, 8 and 10, for checkup and fillings to Dr. Kim. They were reluctant to come. But Dr. Kim was very friendly to them and made them comfortable.

She identified tooth decay, both in initial stages and later stages. She explained available solutions and pros and cons. Both of them got fillings and one of them had his molars sealed. She also discussed possible root cause for the issues.

She explained to the kids the problem with poor brushing. My son has improved his brushing technique after she explained it to him and has promised to drink at least 1.5 ltrs of water every day. This is the kind of personal connection and empathy that I like about her, ***** **** *** **** ****** ** ***********
I appreciate what she has done for my kids and feel lucky to have found her. Would recommend her to anyone looking for a trustworthy dentist.

review.practice_name: Kosmodent Multispeciality Dental Clinic and Implant Centre

review_reply.reply_text: Hi , your case was of failed root canals in two teeth and a worn out bridge above it for your wife ( we have a record of the same as x rays) According to her she had visited multiple clinics before coming to us and she complained that they were not sure of her problem.re rct was done and temporary filling was placed , these are interim restorations are were very much in place when you reported to us. (They are not meant to last for 2 weeks in a grossly decayed teeth)The caps come with 5,10,15 and lifetime warranty and are priced accordingly. Warranties come in writing only when the caps are made. We had always insisted you to be there during her treatment which you failed to do. All the treatments were done with your wife’s consent(including the charges)We understand your concern about pricing ( that’s what you raised in your last visit) if there is any issue with the quality of work pls do revert back and we will be happy to serve you .

He/she is the best
